# Payments — Razorpay

## UPI Flow

**UPI Intent ONLY.** UPI Collect was deprecated in February 2026. Do not scaffold, reference, or implement it under any circumstance.

## Webhook Signature Verification

Mandatory on every Razorpay webhook handler. Reject before any business logic runs.

```typescript
import crypto from 'crypto';

function verifyRazorpaySignature(rawBody: Buffer, signature: string, secret: string): boolean {
  const expected = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret).update(rawBody).digest('hex');
  return crypto.timingSafeEqual(Buffer.from(expected), Buffer.from(signature));
}

// In controller — first line of the handler
if (!verifyRazorpaySignature(rawBody, sig, this.webhookSecret)) {
  throw new UnauthorizedException({ code: 'WEBHOOK_SIGNATURE_INVALID' });
}
```

## Payment State Machine

Transitions must go through the explicit state machine. Never mutate booking status directly from a webhook.

```
pending → processing → success
                     → failed
```

Do NOT touch state machine logic without explicit sign-off — highest-risk area in the codebase.

## Amounts — Integers (Paise) Only

```typescript
// BAD — float, precision loss
amount: 199.99

// GOOD — integer paise
amountPaise: 19999  // ₹199.99
```

All payment amounts stored and transmitted as integers (paise). Never floats.
